{:title "Enhanced Observability Logging"
 :description "Add request correlation IDs, model info, and structured logging for better debugging and traceability"
 :status :todo
 :priority :high
 :created "2026-03-13"
 :tags [:observability :logging :debugging]

 :problem-statement
 "Current logging lacks observability for debugging production issues:
  - No request correlation ID to trace errors to specific requests
  - Model info often missing from log entries
  - No way to correlate logs within a single request flow
  - Errors don't include context needed to debug (what model, what endpoint, etc.)"

 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Every request gets a unique correlation ID (ULID) that's included in all logs for that request"
  "All log entries include :model when the model is known"
  "All log entries include :request-id for correlation"
  "Errors include sufficient context: model, endpoint URL, request ID, error type"
  "Structured JSON logging with consistent schema"
  "Log entries include timestamp in ISO-8601 format with milliseconds"
  "Request/response logging at HTTP boundaries (incoming request, outgoing to LLM, response to client)"
  "Tool execution logging includes server name, tool name, success/failure"
  "Virtual model chain logging shows which provider is being tried"
  "Cooldown events are logged with provider name and duration"]

 :current-state
 "Current log format:
  {:timestamp \"2026-03-13T10:30:00Z\"
   :level \"info\"
   :message \"Chat Completion Started\"
   :data {:model \"gpt-4o-mini\" :stream true}}

  Issues:
  - No request-id to correlate logs
  - Some log points missing :model
  - No :endpoint or :url context in errors
  - Tool execution logged but not tied to specific request"

 :proposed-state
 "Enhanced log format with correlation:
  {:timestamp \"2026-03-13T10:30:00.123Z\"
   :level \"info\"
   :message \"Chat Completion Started\"
   :request-id \"01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV\"
   :model \"gpt-4o-mini\"
   :data {:stream true
          :message-count 2
          :tools-injected [\"stripe.retrieve_customer\"]}}

  Error with full context:
  {:timestamp \"2026-03-13T10:30:00.456Z\"
   :level \"error\"
   :message \"LLM request failed\"
   :request-id \"01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV\"
   :model \"gpt-4o-mini\"
   :endpoint \"http://localhost:8080/v1/chat/completions\"
   :data {:status 429
          :error \"Rate limit exceeded\"
          :retry-after-ms nil}}"

 :edge-cases
 ["What happens when request body is unparseable? Still generate request-id?"
  "What if LLM URL is missing? Log with placeholder"
  "How to handle streaming vs non-streaming in logs?"
  "What if max-iterations reached? Log as warning, not error"
  "Virtual model fallback: log each provider attempt"]

 :implementation-notes
 ["Use ULID for request IDs - sortable, embedded timestamp"
  "Add request-id to all log calls via thread-local or passing through"
  "For agent-loop: pass request-id through all recursive calls"
  "For HTTP errors: include endpoint URL and status code"
  "Virtual model chain: log each provider attempt with :provider field"]

 :depends-on []
 :phases
 [{:phase 1
   :description "Core logging infrastructure"
   :tasks
   ["Add request-id generation at HTTP handler entry"
    "Update log-request to include request-id, model, endpoint"
    "Add request-id to all existing log points in core.clj"]}

  {:phase 2
   :description "Agent loop logging"
   :tasks
   ["Pass request-id through agent-loop function"
    "Log each iteration with request-id"
    "Log tool execution with server name and tool name"
    "Log virtual model chain attempts with provider name"]}

  {:phase 3
   :description "MCP client logging"
   :tasks
   ["Update mcp_client.clj logging to include request-id"
    "Update mcp_client_stdio.clj logging"
    "Ensure all MCP errors include server context"]}

  {:phase 4
   :description "Testing and verification"
   :tasks
   ["Write integration test that verifies request-id in all logs"
    "Test error scenarios include full context"
    "Verify no performance regression from extra logging"]}]

 :tests
 [{:name "request-id-generated-for-every-request"
   :description "Every incoming request gets a unique request-id"}
  {:name "error-includes-model-and-endpoint"
   :description "Errors include model, endpoint URL, and request-id"}
  {:name "tool-execution-logged-with-context"
   :description "Tool calls include server name, tool name, success/failure"}
  {:name "virtual-model-fallback-logged"
   :description "Each provider attempt in chain is logged"}]}
